Job Description:
Software Developer, Ottawa, Canada
Remote work [in Canada] is available*
With over 45,000 employees, Leonardo is a global technology organisation and a key player in the international defence and security market. Leonardo Canada - Electronics is expanding at our location in Ottawa, ON (*) and we have an immediate need for several key resources to support the next phase of our growth. We offer a competitive compensation package and a work environment that supports, encourages and challenges its employees to grow personally.

Remote-location work arrangement - in Canada - during the Pandemic. Option to discuss continued remote work once the restrictions have been lifted.
For additional information on Leonardo, please visit our website at www.leonardocompany.ca (http://www.leonardocompany.ca/)

We are currently hiring multiple Software Developers, for exciting opportunities to actively contribute to the ongoing design and development of our core products within the Electronics Warfare domain. As a member of the engineering team, you will integrate into our growing agile scrum team.
The role may also require participation in various project relates meetings and reviews such as customer facing design reviews and supporting internal and external test events.

Your role:
Build new software components and services that seamlessly integrate user interface with backend services;
Write clean code that effectively communicates its own functionality;
Help improve our quality by making necessary improvements to our code and our processes;
Participate in our Scrum ceremonies, design sessions and code reviews;
Assist in the allocation of system requirements to software components;
Effectively communicate technical and product knowledge to stakeholders at various levels such as engineers, product managers, engineering managers, architects and upper management;
Collaborate with team members in discovering best practices and patterns for continuous improvement; and
Maintain a strong sense of accountability and ownership of the solutions produced.
What We Are Looking For:
Experience as a Software Developer building distributed solutions;
Solid understanding of software development lifecycle and processes in agile development environment using methodologies (Scrum, Kanban) and tools (Jira, Bitbucket, Jenkins and Nexus);
Experience developing in any or all of the following languages: GoLang, Javascript, HMTL and CSS;
Experience with relational databases (eg PostgreSQL, SQL); and
Excellent interpersonal, written/verbal communication and customer interaction skills.
The “nice to haves”:
Knowledge/experience with Software automation (CI/CD pipeline);
Knowledge/experience using Docker, Kubernetes;
Knowledge/experience with the VMWare technologies; and
Experience contributing to technical design documentation.
Security Clearance
It is a condition of employment that the successful candidate receive a secret level security clearance.

To obtain such a clearance, the candidate:
Must be either a Canadian citizen or permanent resident of Canada;
Must have lived in Canada continuously for the past 10 years & not have a criminal record;
Must be able to obtain a Canadian Industrial Security Clearance to NATO SECRET level;
Must be eligible for International Traffic in Arms Regulations (ITAR) and Controlled Goods Regulations Program (CGRP) government clearances.
If your qualifications meet the job description & key requirements, we'd love to hear from you!

Job Type: Full-time, Permanent
Please submit your application on-line today.

Special needs of candidates with disabilities will be accommodated. Successful candidates must fulfill requirements for Canadian Controlled Goods Program (CGP) and Canadian Security Clearance. Leonardo supports the principles of employment equity and is an equal opportunity employer. Please apply to this position as indicated. Visit us at https://leonardocompany.ca/
